[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has five cards in each Major and NORTH opens 1NT.

First SOUTH bids 2\H, indicating a 5-card \S suit with the Transfer bid. 
Then, after NORTH bids the obligatory 2\S, SOUTH jumps to 4\H, promising 
enough strength for game, and also five \Hs to go with the five \Ss.

NORTH prefers \Ss, so she corrects the contract to 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:A96.KQ62.K532.K8 JT87.A94.QJ6.T52 KQ542.87.A8.Q764 3.JT53.T974.AJ93"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 3NT pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "ef7600392606ab185b20dc34c8d664259bce37145450f45041c9b5973a3836f4"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{With 12 points and five \Ss, when WEST hears her partner open 1NT she knows 
there is a game - either 3NT or 4\S.

WEST first transfers EAST to \Ss, then jumps to 3NT, giving EAST the choice. 

EAST has three \Ss, so he chooses 4\S, taking the 8-card Major fit.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:K86.A93.KQ8.AKJ2 AQ2.T6.654.T8654 74.KQJ7542.A92.9 JT953.8.JT73.Q73"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2NT pass 3D pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5H pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "ff2958842344390c42890f81f21d918ee299e8216042dbad3edfb9567b6a4028"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{After SOUTH opens 2NT, NORTH is pretty sure there will be a slam in \Hs. 
But, the contract should be played from the SOUTH side so the opening lead doesn't go through any vulnerable 
\S holding SOUTH might have.

NORTH transfers SOUTH to \Hs, then uses Blackwood to be sure they aren't 
off two Aces. Missing one Ace he settles for 6\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
